@startuml
!include ../style.puml

actor "Client Alice" as Alice
participant "Node 1\n(Partition 1)" as P1
participant "Node 2\n(Partition 2)" as P2

note over Alice: Transaction Goal:\n1. Deduct $100 from Account1 (P1)\n2. Add $100 to Account2 (P2)

'[step {"name": "Step 1: Write to Partition 1"}]
== Step 1: Write to Partition 1 ==
Alice -> P1: Update Account1 (-$100)
'[step {"name": "Step 1: Gets Success"}]
P1 --> Alice: Success

'[step {"name": "Step 2: Write to Partition 2"}]

== Step 2: Write to Partition 2 ==
Alice -> P2: Update Account2 (+$100)
'[step {"name": "Step 2: Gets Error / Timeout"}]
note right of P2: Node 2 crashes or\nnetwork times out
Alice x-- P2: Error / Timeout

note over Alice, P2: SYSTEM IS INCONSISTENT:\nAccount1 lost $100, but Account2 didn't get it.\n(Atomicity is broken)
@enduml
